    <section id="tribute-info">
      <p>
        Dr. Avul Pakir Jainulabdeen Abdul Kalam (1931–2015) was a prominent Indian aerospace scientist and the 11th President of India. He played a key role in India's Pokhran-II nuclear tests and was celebrated for his humility, vision, and dedication to youth development. He authored several inspirational books like "Wings of Fire" and "Ignited Minds". Known as the "Missile Man of India", he inspired millions with his scientific contributions and motivational thoughts.
      </p>
    </section>

